scopecontent.p:
The section contains drawings published in serials, either as illustrations for stories by various authors or as Newell's own comics. They are arranged by the name of the magazine in which they were published, and within that by the author of the story. Many of the drawings remain in their presentation mats showing story captions and editor's markings. Numbers in parentheses following the story titles indicate the number of drawings extant in this collection out of the number of illustrations published (in some cases more drawings were made than were published). Several of the serialized stories illustrated by Newell were later issued as novels (such as Frank Stockton's 
                        The Great Stone of Sardis
                     ) or as humor collections (like Carolyn Wells's 
                        The Merry-Go-Round
                     ); drawings for these works appear in the "Books" section above.

